  "name": "Paris in Danger",
  "shortName": "paris-in-danger",
  "description": "<i>Paris in Danger</i> recreates the 1814 campaign against Napoleon's France, when allied Russian, Prussian and Austrian forces of the Sixth Coalition were marching towards Paris. It is played on both strategical (on a map of entire France and today's western Germany; corps size units) and tactical level (battles, which can be also resolved automatically; division size units), from either side of the conflict. Effects of morale, unit facing and formation are taken into account.<br>\nThe players gain victory points (the French for killing enemies, the Allies for capturing cities), which are summed up after 25 turns (each lasting few days) to declare the winner.",
